    "When s t = 1, the human prefers the first response; and when s t = 0, the human prefers the second one.",
    "The regularization strength γ > 0 is set automatically by cross-validation.",
    "The two-headed BTL (BTL2) judge is a BTL judge that estimates the preferred response from two separate absolute evaluations.",
    "This builds on the findings that pointwise evaluators tend to be more robust (Jeong et al., 2024), while pairwise evaluators are more susceptible to superficial cues due to inherent biases in LLMs (Wang et al., 2024a; Chiang and Lee, 2023).",
